laboratory_examinations.findings: FSH levels ranged from 6.7 to 19.1 mIU/mL; LH levels ranged from 5.8 to 15.1 mIU/mL. Both FSH and LH remained mildly elevated.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: There has been no dramatic change in LH and FSH levels over the years.

laboratory_examinations.findings: E2 levels ranged from 3,500 to 47 pg/mL; E1 levels ranged from 1,040 to 1,050 pg/mL.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: E2 decreased from 1910 to 47 pg/mL after norethindrone treatment.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Z-scores of -3.8 at age 15 years and -4.3 at age 23 years, indicating significant reduction in bone mineral density.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Bone density continued to decrease with z-scores becoming more negative over time.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Mean ovarian volume ranged from 38.2 to 123.7 cm³; normal is <20 cm³.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Ovarian volume decreased from 123.7 to 10.5 cm³ after treatment with norethindrone.
